ABOUT UserLib

	UserLib is a C++ Framework with a C-Kernel. I can easily and quickly write an application.
	If you like the library, you can do the same. If you need any help, write me an email.

	OK, the main domain where the library lives is windows desktop, and it runs under Mingw and Cygwin.
	I am interested to see it running under linux.

FEATURE List

	- am memory manager for small objects (C)
	- data structures including AVL-trees, RB-trees and B*-trees (C, C++)
	- string utilities including CStringBuffer (C, C++)
	- application and program option management (C++)
	- and many more ...

DIRECTORY structure

	UserLib/
	 +-- CSources/
	 +-- CppSources/
	 +-- WinSources/
	 +-- ConSources/
	 +-- GuiSources/
	 +
	 +-- ... sample applications

HOWTO install

	See the file INSTALL for instructions on how to build and install UserLib. 
	That file also lists supported compilers and operating systems and contains 
	information regarding any other software packages that are required to build 
	or run the Library.  Copyright and license information can be found in the
	files COPYING.LESSER and COPYING. 
